
1. Use proper naming. CamelCase, with Svd prefix for all custom ServeD classes.

2. User A wont (and never should) know everything about user B's work. (Share knowledge about what You did with rest of team! "man synergy")

3. It should work first. Then beautify it and optimize. (Prevent premature optimization!)

4. Optimize when code (or part of code/ module) is in production stage of development only.

5. Stability is more important than performance

6. Git "master" branch, should always be production ready